							<!-- End each blog post -->
							
														
							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/daisy-dunn/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/daisy-dunn-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" alt="Daisy Dunn" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/daisy-dunn/">Daisy Dunn</a></h6>
										Daisy Dunn is an award-winning classicist and the author of <em>The Missing Thread: A Women's History of the Ancient World</em>, <em>The Shadow of Vesuvius: A Life of Pliny</em>, <em>Catullus’ Bedspread: The Life of Rome’s Most Erotic Poet</em>, and <em>The Poems of Catullus: A New Translation</em>. She read Classics at Oxford before receiving an MA in the History of Art from the Courtauld Institute and her PhD from UCL. She lives in London, England. Her website is www.daisydunn.co.uk.																				<div class="website">
			    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
				    						<a href="http://www.daisydunn.co.uk" target="_blank" class="external">http://www.daisydunn.co.uk</a>
				    					</div>
				    														</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
